%TUTORIAL -`-`- ZIL - COMPILER OPTIONS -`-`- TUTORIAL
%SELECTION ===>_ZCMD
+
%Show TRNLIST? Y or N
!Y+specifies that you wish to see the output of the source transformation phase
 of the ZIL compiler.  !N+specifies that you do not.  (The compiler invokes the
 transformations regardless of what you specify here.)

%Show ZILLIST? Y or N
!Y+specifies that you wish to browse the ZIL compiler listing. !N+specifies
 that you do not.  If the compilation fails, the listing will be browsed
 regardless.

%Show ASMLIST? Y or N
!Y+specifies that you wish to browse the listing produced by the assembler when
 the output of the ZIL compiler is assembled.  !N+specifies that you do not.
 If the assembly fails, the listing will be browsed regardless.

%Show LNKLIST? Y or N
!Y+specifies that you wish to browse the linkage editor listing.  !N+specifies
 that you do not. If the linkedit fails, the listing will be browsed regardless.

